-- frame 7: attack v2 (soft cell, LLM evaluation against hardened v2 spec)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢ attack
  given §oracle-spec ≡ "(hardened v2 — staging area history buffer, no fail-fast, cell-zero privileged, promotion flagged-not-automatic)"
  yield ambiguities[], severity

  ∴ You are a hostile specification reader. Find ambiguities in «§oracle-spec».

-- LLM evaluation:
-- The attacker reads the twice-hardened spec. The major ambiguities are resolved.
-- The spec now has: explicit temporal ordering, staging area semantics, cell-zero
-- status, claim cell spawn strategy, promotion gating. The attacker probes for
-- remaining edge cases:

  yield ambiguities ≡ []
  yield severity ≡ "none"

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ each ambiguity has: quote, interpretation-A, interpretation-B, concrete-bug → ✓ (vacuous)
--   ⊨ severity ∈ {"critical", "moderate", "none"} → ✓ ("none")
