-- attack→severity = "none" → ⊢∘ TERMINATES. Spec is hardened.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- COMPLETE: 8 eval-one steps across 3 ⊢∘ iterations
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
-- Iteration 0 (severity: critical, 4 ambiguities):
--   "spawns after evaluation" timing, tentative output ownership,
--   cell-zero nature, automatic crystallization
--   → All 4 fixed by defender, all 4 accepted by judge
--
-- Iteration 1 (severity: moderate, 2 ambiguities):
--   staging area semantics (buffer vs log), claim cell spawn strategy
--   → Both fixed, both accepted
--
-- Iteration 2 (severity: none, 0 ambiguities):
--   Attacker finds no more ambiguities → ⊢∘ terminates
--
-- The spec grew from ~30 lines to ~50 lines. Each addition was FORCED by a
-- concrete ambiguity that a hostile reader identified. No bloat — every new
-- sentence closes a real loophole.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- OBSERVATIONS
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢= obs-adversarial-convergence
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "ADVERSARIAL LOOPS CONVERGE: severity went critical → moderate → none in 3 iterations. The attacker found 4 ambiguities in v0, 2 in v1, 0 in v2. Each hardening pass reduced the attack surface. This is the spec equivalent of a fuzzer finding fewer crashes over time — the attack surface shrinks monotonically because fixes are additive (new precision) not subtractive (removing features)."

⊢= obs-meta-circularity
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "CELL HARDENED ITS OWN SPEC: the Oracle System section of the Cell v0.1 spec was hardened BY a Cell program. The ambiguities found are REAL — 'spawns after evaluation' IS ambiguous, cell-zero's nature IS underspecified, oracle promotion IS unclear about automation. A Cell program discovered genuine defects in Cell's own specification. This is metacircular validation: the language found bugs in its own definition."

⊢= obs-three-role-separation
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "THREE ROLES ARE NECESSARY: attack (find), defend (fix), judge (verify). Merging attack+defend creates conflicts of interest — the fixer knows the bugs and can write fixes that LOOK good but don't actually eliminate the ambiguity. Merging defend+judge removes adversarial pressure — the fixer grades their own work. The three-role separation is the minimum for trustworthy spec hardening. Cell's dataflow graph makes this separation natural: each role is a cell with explicit inputs and outputs."

⊢= obs-evolution-as-adversarial
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "⊢∘ GENERALIZES BEYOND SELF-IMPROVEMENT: in program 02, ⊢∘ improved a prompt via judge+improve (cooperative). Here, ⊢∘ hardens a spec via attack+defend+judge (adversarial). Same mechanism, different topology. The until condition changed from 'score ≥ 8' (quality threshold) to 'severity = none' (attack surface eliminated). ⊢∘ is a general fixed-point combinator — it doesn't care whether the loop is cooperative or adversarial, only that it converges."

⊢= obs-spec-growth-as-signal
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "SPEC GROWTH IS A QUALITY SIGNAL: the Oracle System section grew from ~30 to ~50 lines. But growth was NOT bloat — every addition was forced by a concrete ambiguity with two contradictory interpretations and a real implementor bug. If the defender adds text that doesn't close an ambiguity, the judge rejects it. Growth under adversarial pressure is specification DENSITY increasing — more precision per line, more lines because precision demands it."

⊢= obs-exhaustion-meaning
  yield observation
  ⊢= observation ← "ATTACKER EXHAUSTION = SPEC COMPLETENESS (for this attacker): severity='none' means THIS attacker, at THIS capability level, found no more ambiguities. A stronger attacker might find more. This is the fundamental limit of adversarial testing — completeness is relative to attacker capability. The max 4 bound on ⊢∘ is a safety net, not a quality gate. True termination came from attacker exhaustion at iteration 2, not from hitting the bound."
